===Etymology 1===
{{PIE root|en|(s)ker|id=cut}}
From {{inh|en|enm|screde}}{{nb...|screade (Kent)|otherforms=1}}, a variant of {{m|enm|shrede|t=fragment, scrap; strip of cloth; strip cut off from a larger piece; band or thread woven into fabric; element, streak}} (whence {{m|en|shred|pos=noun}}),<ref name="MED">{{R:MED Online|entry=shrēde|pos=n|id=MED40099}}</ref><ref>{{R:OED Online|pos=''n.''{{sup|1}}|noformat=1|id=173431|date=March 2017|nodot=1}}; {{R:Lexico|pos=n}}</ref> from {{inh|en|ang|sċrēad}}, {{m|ang|sċrēade|t=a piece cut off; paring, shred}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*skraudō|t=a piece, shred; a cut, crack}}, from {{m|gem-pro|*skraudaną|t=to cut up, shred}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*(s)ker-|t=to cut off}}. The English word is cognate with {{cog|ofs|skrēd}}.<ref name="MED"/>

